Interactive CLI for the xAI Grok API.
- Read user input via input_handler (show "grok> " prompt, quit on "quit" or EOF)
- Store conversation history in context_store (user and assistant messages as strings)
- Call the Grok API via api_caller using curl with JSON chat completions format
  (POST to https://api.x.ai/v1/chat/completions with Authorization: Bearer $XAI_API_KEY)
- Buffer streaming responses through response_buffer
- Parse the JSON response to extract the assistant's message content
- Print assistant responses, loop until user quits
- Use XAI_API_KEY env var for auth (exit with error if not set)
- Use XAI_MODEL env var for model (default grok-4-0709)
- Maintain multi-turn conversation by sending full message history each request
- Handle JSON escaping for user input (escape quotes, backslashes, newlines)
- Rotate oldest messages when context_store is full
- Handle SIGINT (Ctrl+C) gracefully: install a signal handler that prints a newline and exits cleanly with code 0 instead of crashing
